y followed by bottomup stockpicking based on intensive fundamental research and an extensive program of company visitsthe companies in which ward ferry invests are evaluated comparatively to the industry for long picks the firm looks for strong fundamentals and superior management in reasonablyvalued companies that have a competitive advantage key drivers are return on equity free cash flow dividend yields and pricetobook ratio among the criteria for shorting are deteriorating earnings and cost of capital exceeding return on investmentward ferry aims for less volatility than the msci asia pacific free index chief investment officer prior lloyd george management hong kong ltd lgmhk is an active garporiented manager which follows a fundamental researchintensive investment strategy to select stocks they aim to outperform in asian and global emerging markets during periods of strong performance and preserve clients capital when market volatility is higher concentrating on small to midcap equitiesthe firm follows a team approach to investment management and select stocks by concentrating on key quantitative and qualitative drivers including company management knowledge teams located in the areas where they invest a mix of bottomup stockpicking and a global macro viewpoint as well as a risk control process developed for asia and global emerging markets investmentsmanager performance is monitored by the lgmhk senior stock selection committee boards  committees corporate boards ▾ director  executive chairman   current ward ferry management ltd ward ferry is a conservative alternative investment manager they invest primarily in securities that are listed quoted or traded on asian exchanges and overthecounter markets as well as in american or global depositary receipts of asian companies the firm also invests in fixedincome issued by governments and corporations they invest marginally in other funds and use derivatives for hedging purposesthe firm manages longshort equity hed